<!-- §9 What is a sunset lamp projector -->
<h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">What is a Sunset Lamp Projector?</h2>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">A sunset lamp projector is a compact, typically USB-powered device that emits ambient light in sunset or rainbow color gradients. Unlike traditional light bulbs, projectors cast a soft glow across a wall or ceiling, creating depth and atmosphere rather than direct illumination.</p>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The USB Sunset Rainbow Projector specifically offers 16 color modes that cycle automatically. Place it on a shelf, point it at a blank wall, plug it in, and it runs continuously. No app, no Wi-Fi, no configuration—just pure aesthetic.</p>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">These have become wildly popular in dorm rooms, bedrooms, and content creator studios because they're affordable, look great on camera, and transform space instantly. Think of it as the visual equivalent of ambient music—it sets a mood without demanding attention.</p>

