    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.5;">Remove the projector from the box. Find a spot on a shelf, desk, nightstand, or dresser—anywhere flat and stable. Position it 2–3 feet away from the wall you want to light up. The farther away, the larger the light coverage, but the dimmer the spread. For a bedroom, aim it at a blank wall above your headboard or at a corner.</p>
