<!-- FAQ -->
<h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem;">
  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Is the USB Sunset Rainbow Projector safe to use?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Yes, it's completely safe. The projector operates at ≤36V—well below the 48V threshold that requires electrical safety precautions. USB power is inherently safer than wall-powered devices. It generates minimal heat and poses no fire risk. Safe for bedrooms, children's rooms, and dorms. Just keep it away from water and extreme heat, and ensure the USB cable isn't damaged.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Will this work for TikTok and content creation?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Absolutely. The rainbow and sunset colors look incredible on camera, especially in dynamic lighting. Many TikTok creators use this exact product for room tours, dance backgrounds, and aesthetic videos. Position it to one side of your shot and angle it toward a blank wall for maximum visual impact. The automatic color cycling creates movement that reads beautifully on video.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Can I pick a single color or control it with an app?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">No app, no remote color selection. Colors cycle automatically through all 16 modes. You can press the button to jump to the next mode, but you can't lock onto one color or pause the cycle. If you need granular color control, the App-Controlled Galaxy Star Projector ($62) lets you pick any color via smartphone app.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">How bright is it and how far does the light throw?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">The projector is ideal for mood lighting, not task lighting. From 2–3 feet away, it covers roughly 3–4 feet in diameter on the wall. Perfect for accenting one wall or corner, not suitable for lighting an entire room. Use it alongside a desk lamp or overhead light if you need visibility for work or reading.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">How does it compare to the App-Controlled Star Projector?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">The App-Controlled Star Projector ($62, Vibe Score 87) offers Wi-Fi connectivity, app color selection, rotation patterns, and greater throw distance. It's a serious home setup tool. The USB Sunset Rainbow Projector ($25.50, Vibe Score 68) trades features for price and simplicity—plug in and go, no app setup. Pick based on your needs: quick ambiance? Go Sunset. Smart home integration? Go Star.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">What's included in the box?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">USB Sunset Rainbow Projector, USB power cable (typically 1–2 meters), and a basic instruction manual. Some listings include a remote control; check the product variant to confirm. No batteries required.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">How long will the LED bulb last before it burns out?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">LED projectors typically last 50,000+ hours — roughly 20+ years of continuous operation. The LED is unlikely to be the limiting factor. The USB cable and electronic components are what might fail first. Treat it well and it should last for years.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Can I use an extension cord with this projector?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Yes. You can use any standard USB-A extension cord to extend the cable length. Since it operates at low voltage (safe), there are no electrical safety concerns with longer cables. A 10-15 foot extension is standard and works fine.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Is this better than a regular lamp for bedroom ambiance?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">It depends on your goals. This projector creates dynamic, colorful ambient light that transforms a wall. A regular lamp provides more practical task lighting but less visual drama. For pure mood and aesthetics, this beats a standard lamp. For reading or daily tasks, you'll want both.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Does this projector attract bugs or insects?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">LED light is less attractive to insects than incandescent bulbs, but it can still attract some bugs if used outdoors. For indoor use (bedroom, dorm), this is not a concern. If you use it near an open window, expect minor insect attention.</p>
    </div>
  </details>
</div>

